

This is an NFSv4 server, that serves data from RAM.



[Minimalist] project home page
------------------------------

	http://linux.yyz.us/projects/nfsv4.html


Official source code repository
-------------------------------

	git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/daemon/nfs/nfs4-ram.git


Dependencies
------------
	GLib 2.0.0 or later (http://www.gtk.org/)
	GNet 2.0.5 or later (http://www.gnetlibrary.org/)


Building the server
-------------------

	./autogen.sh
	CFLAGS="-O2 -Wall -g" ./configure
	make
	make install

Depending on your RPC configuration, the tests may or may not work for
you:

	make check

Test fixes and other contributions are welcomed!


Using the server
----------------

	./nfs4_ramd

will create an empty RAM-based filesystem, served via NFS v4, on the
default NFS TCP port (2049).


Additional configuration options
--------------------------------
Besides the command line options (./nfs4_ramd --help), this is a
zero-configuration daemon.  No need to set up any configuration files.

